<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R2-025" project="SprkChat Platform Enhancement R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Deploy Phase 2 — BFF API Build, Test, and Deployment to Dev Environment</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>deploy, azure, bff-api</tags>
    <estimated-effort>medium</estimated-effort>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Deployment task — STANDARD rigor applies; follows the established bff-deploy skill pattern; requires test verification and smoke tests but not full implementation rigor</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>[010, 011, 012, 013, 014, 015, 016, 017, 018, 019, 020, 021, 022, 023, 024]</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build, test, and deploy all Phase 2 BFF API changes to the dev environment. Verify the new
    endpoints and services are accessible and functioning after deployment.

    **Build and test**:
    1. Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — MUST succeed with no errors
    2. Run `dotnet test tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` (or equivalent test project) — MUST pass; new failures
       introduced by Phase 2 work must be fixed before deployment
    3. Run `dotnet format --verify-no-changes` — verify code formatting compliance

    **Deploy**:
    4. Run `scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1` to publish and deploy to the dev App Service (`spe-api-dev-67e2xz`)
    5. Verify deployment success: check App Service health (`GET /healthz`) returns 200

    **Smoke tests** (manual verification after deployment):
    6. SSE streaming: send a test chat message and verify token-by-token streaming in the response
    7. Document upload: upload a small PDF (test fixture) to `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/documents`
       and verify 202 Accepted response with documentId
    8. Playbook dispatch: verify `POST /api/ai/playbooks/{playbookId}/index` endpoint is accessible
       (returns 202 for a valid playbookId, 404 for non-existent)
    9. Word export: send a test markdown payload to `POST /api/ai/chat/export/word` and verify
       201 Created response with wordOnlineUrl
    10. Verify typing_start/typing_end SSE events appear in a streaming response

    **Rollback criteria**: If health check fails or any smoke test returns 5xx, roll back by
    redeploying the previous build artifact. Document rollback in `notes/025-deployment-log.md`.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with Azure AI and Minimal API expertise</role>

  <goal>
    Phase 2 BFF API changes are deployed to the dev environment. All smoke tests pass. The dev
    environment is ready for Phase 3 frontend development and Phase 4 integration testing.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="Project specification — NFR-01 through NFR-08, deployment environment details">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="Project AI context — deployment approach, BFF endpoint, App Service name">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="BFF API deployment script">scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1</file>
    <file purpose="BFF deploy skill — deployment procedure">../.claude/skills/bff-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
    <file purpose="Azure resource documentation — App Service name, health check endpoint">docs/architecture/auth-azure-resources.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST run `dotnet test` and verify all tests pass before deployment — no deployment with failing tests</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md">MUST use `scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1` for BFF deployment — do NOT use `az webapp deploy` directly without the script</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">BFF API endpoint: `https://spe-api-dev-67e2xz.azurewebsites.net` — health check: `GET /healthz`</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">If deployment fails (health check 5xx), MUST roll back before marking task complete</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/auth-azure-resources.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern>BFF deploy sequence: dotnet publish → copy artifacts → Deploy-BffApi.ps1 → verify health check — follow the bff-deploy SKILL.md procedure exactly</pattern>
      <pattern>Health check verification: `curl -s https://spe-api-dev-67e2xz.azurewebsites.net/healthz` should return `{"status":"Healthy"}` within 60 seconds of deployment</pattern>
      <pattern>Smoke test for SSE endpoint: use curl with `--no-buffer -H "Accept: text/event-stream"` to observe token streaming in terminal output</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Phase 2 introduces 16 tasks worth of BFF API changes: new endpoints (document upload, SPE persist,
      Word export, playbook index), new services (DocumentContextService, PlaybookDispatcher,
      PlaybookOutputHandler, DynamicCommandResolver, AnalysisChatContextResolver), and enhanced
      existing services (WebSearchTools, WorkingDocumentTools, ChatEndpoints, DocxExportService).

      This deployment task consolidates all Phase 2 work into a single dev environment deployment
      so that Phase 3 frontend development can target the deployed API. Phase 3 and Phase 4 tasks
      require the Phase 2 endpoints to be live in the dev environment.

      The `scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1` script handles the publish, package, and App Service deployment
      steps. The bff-deploy SKILL.md contains the full deployment procedure. Follow it.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Depends on ALL Phase 2 implementation tasks: R2-010 through R2-024. This is the last Phase 2
      task. Phase 3 tasks (R2-030 through R2-045) and Phase 4 tasks depend on this deployment
      completing successfully.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Load `.claude/skills/bff-deploy/SKILL.md` to confirm the exact deployment procedure for this environment</step>
    <step order="1">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ --configuration Release` — fix any build errors before proceeding</step>
    <step order="2">Run `dotnet test` (or the equivalent test command for this project) — fix any new test failures introduced by Phase 2 changes</step>
    <step order="3">Run `dotnet format --verify-no-changes src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — fix formatting issues if any</step>
    <step order="4">Run `scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1` to deploy to the dev App Service</step>
    <step order="5">Wait for deployment to complete; verify health check: `GET https://spe-api-dev-67e2xz.azurewebsites.net/healthz` returns 200</step>
    <step order="6">Smoke test SSE streaming: send a test message and observe token-by-token response</step>
    <step order="7">Smoke test document upload: POST a test PDF to the upload endpoint, verify 202 Accepted</step>
    <step order="8">Smoke test playbook indexing: POST to `/api/ai/playbooks/{knownPlaybookId}/index`, verify 202 Accepted</step>
    <step order="9">Smoke test Word export: POST test markdown to `/api/ai/chat/export/word`, verify 201 Created with wordOnlineUrl</step>
    <step order="10">If any smoke test returns 5xx: investigate logs in App Service, fix the issue, re-deploy (do NOT mark task complete with failing smoke tests)</step>
    <step order="11">Create a git commit with all Phase 2 BFF changes: `git add` the modified/new files, commit with message summarizing Phase 2 BFF implementation</step>
    <step order="12">Document deployment outcome in `notes/025-deployment-log.md`: timestamp, build version, smoke test results</step>
    <step order="13">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task R2-025 status to completed (🔲 → ✅)</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>dotnet</tool>
    <tool>git</tool>
    <tool>az</tool>
    <tool>pwsh</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <artifact type="config">Phase 2 BFF API deployed to `spe-api-dev-67e2xz.azurewebsites.net`</artifact>
    <artifact type="docs">notes/025-deployment-log.md — deployment log with timestamp, build version, and smoke test results</artifact>
    <artifact type="code">Git commit — all Phase 2 BFF API implementation changes committed</artifact>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` returns exit code 0 with no errors</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet test` passes with no new failures (existing failures are pre-existing and documented)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`GET https://spe-api-dev-67e2xz.azurewebsites.net/healthz` returns HTTP 200 after deployment</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Chat streaming endpoint returns `typing_start` event followed by `token` events (SSE smoke test)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Document upload endpoint returns `202 Accepted` with a `documentId` in the response body</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Word export endpoint returns `201 Created` with a `wordOnlineUrl` field</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All Phase 2 BFF changes are committed to git on the `work/ai-sprk-chat-workspace-companion` branch</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The App Service `spe-api-dev-67e2xz` is in resource group `spe-infrastructure-westus2`.
    The `scripts/Deploy-BffApi.ps1` script handles the complete deployment — do not try to
    deploy manually unless the script fails and the SKILL.md has documented fallback steps.

    For smoke tests, you will need a valid test session ID and user credentials. Check
    `docs/guides/` for the dev environment test credentials or request them from the team if
    they are not documented. Alternatively, run the smoke tests with the integration test
    infrastructure if it supports testing against the deployed dev environment.

    After successful deployment, notify the Phase 3 frontend developer that the Phase 2 BFF
    endpoints are live and ready for integration. Provide the endpoint URLs and the SSE event
    contract from `notes/018-new-sse-event-types.md` and `notes/023-writeback-sse-events.md`.
  </notes>

